  <num>38-1202.04</num>
  <heading>Reimbursement of Trustees.</heading>
  <text>Trustees shall serve without compensation except that each Trustee shall be entitled to reimbursement for actual and necessary expenses incurred while actually engaged in service as a Trustee, provided that these expenses are properly documented. In no case, however, shall a Trustee receive expense reimbursement that exceeds $4,000 per annum.</text>
